body.name: Beyond Honor (Book 1: Galaxy At War): A Military Sci-Fi Novel
body.description: TWO SWORN ENEMIES. ONE CHANCE TO SAVE THE GALAXY.In the midst of an unforgiving galactic war, Joel Chambers and his unit never expected their greatest challenge to come from beneath their feet. While engaged in a fierce skirmish on a primitive planet, their reality is upended as a mysterious starship bursts from the ground, altering the course of their mission — and the war itself.Suddenly, survival demands the unthinkable: an alliance with their sworn enemies. Chambers, leading his beleaguered team, must navigate this precarious truce in pursuit of a formidable adversary, one whose power threatens to shift the interstellar balance of power.But cooperation is easier said than done when tensions run high and old grudges die hard. As they chase a threat that weaves through the stars, the line between ally and enemy blurs.In a universe where trust is scarce and betrayal is just one misstep away, can they put aside their differences long enough to avert a cosmic catastrophe?Beyond Honor is a military science fiction series full of action, humor, and mystery. If you're looking for an adventure that starts with a gunfight and ends with galactic consequences, this is the series for you!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewText: A planet where the inhabitants are not up to a certain scientific level yet and protected, is the location for the strangest of confrontations yet. On the one hand there is Unit Zero sent to retrieve a missing scientist. The there is the Vanguard unit from the enemy on a mission to kill a scientist.Both teams sent to the same spot with almost similar goals.And both military teams got ambushed in the weirdest of circumstances.To survive and accomplish their respective goals, these two teams have to forget they are enemies bound to kill each other. Instead they have to work together.But can they?Beyond Honor Book 1 is a surprise chapter by chapter, keeping the reader entranced all the time as surprise after surprise keeps on happening.Enjoy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The first book of an exciting new series
reviews.reviewText: Enemies thrown together and forced to ally in order to rescue their commanders and possibly save the galaxy. Two units of special forces operatives: the human “Zero Unit” and the Arcadian “Vanguard” unit meet unexpectedly at the same primitive planet, each with the same mission: retrieve their scientist that had been sent there to observe a primitive society. Things begin to go wrong almost immediately as both teams find themselves working together to save the galaxy as they are being hunted for crimes they did not commit. This book is typical of books written by Daniel Young and the reader should find plenty of action and a fast moving story that will grab hold of the reader and usually includes a cliff hanging plot twist at the end.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great beginning of a series!
reviews.reviewText: Two opposing secret military teams are after the same thing. What happens when they show up at the same time? That is what you find out when you read this book ( hint- mayhem!). Although I make it sound simplistic, it is actually an intricate weaving of give and take between the two teams and the obstacles they both face. Most of the action takes place planet-side, where most of the evil resides.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Exciting but … Cliffhanger Ending
reviews.reviewText: BEYOND HONOR (GALAXY AT WAR Book 1) is an entertaining action filled, battle-after-battle, enemies to comrades space military tale. It keeps the reader turning pages right to the last page. Unfortunately, the last page is a cliffhanger. I hate cliffhangers.Disclosure: I received a free copy of this book with no strings attached.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Enjoyed it tremendously. Keep reading always finding ways to not stop. Held me captive until the very end page. Leaving me wanting more!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Another series begins full of action and adventure as our heroes make choices and try to survive to the end. Entertaining and easy to get sucked into the series as meet all the characters and figure out what is going on. What crazy things would happen next kept me glued to the end. I received an early copy and loved it.

reviews.reviewTitle: A story of twists and turns
reviews.reviewText: The line line between friends and foes gets blurred - loyalties change - just being able to survive becomes paramoint. Definitely looking forward to the next episode in a few weeks.
